		            		            		            					<!-- start content -->
					<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="Simple_Returns">Simple Returns</span></h2>
<p>Let $$P&#95;t$$ denote the price in month $$t$$ of an asset that pays no dividends and let $$P&#95;{t−1}$$ denote the price in month $$t − 1$$.</p>
<p>$$R = \frac{(P&#95;t - P&#95;{t-1})}{P&#95;{t-1}}$$</p>
<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="Continuously_Compounded_Returns">Continuously Compounded Returns</span></h2>
<p>Let $$P&#95;t$$ denote the price in month $$t$$ of an asset that pays no dividends and let $$P&#95;{t−1}$$ denote the price in month $$t − 1$$.</p>
<p>$$r = \ln\left(\frac{P&#95;t}{P&#95;{t-1}}\right)$$</p>

